### Minimal 8-step smoke test for local microservices
### Run in order.

@baseEureka = http://localhost:8761
@baseGateway = http://localhost:8081
@baseMonolith = http://localhost:8080
@smokeUser = smoke_gateway_user
@smokeEmail = smoke_gateway_user@example.com
@smokePassword = TestPassword123

### 1) Eureka UI reachable (expect 200)
GET {{baseEureka}}

###
### 2) Auth service registered in Eureka (expect 200)
GET {{baseEureka}}/eureka/apps/AUTH-SERVICE

###
### 3) API Gateway registered in Eureka (expect 200)
GET {{baseEureka}}/eureka/apps/API-GATEWAY

###
### 4) API Gateway health (expect 200)
GET {{baseGateway}}/actuator/health

###
### 5) Monolith health (expect 200)
GET {{baseMonolith}}/actuator/health

###
### 6) Register user through gateway (expect 201 first run, 409 if already exists)
POST {{baseGateway}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{smokeUser}}",
  "email": "{{smokeEmail}}",
  "password": "{{smokePassword}}"
}

###
### 7) Login through gateway (expect 200)
POST {{baseGateway}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{smokeUser}}",
  "password": "{{smokePassword}}"
}

> {%
client.global.set("jwt", response.body.token);
%}

###
### 8) Quantity route through gateway with token (expect 200)
GET {{baseGateway}}/api/v1/quantities/history/errored
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt}}

